<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="253" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="50.[114,646,1215,1433]" pageId="50" pageNumber="253">
DIAGNOSIS. — 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borojevic &amp; Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" box="[267,357,1282,1306]" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="50" pageNumber="253" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Baeriidae</taxonomicName>
in which the choanoskeleton consists of microdiactines. Cortical and atrial skeletons have triactines and tetractines, and the cortex is pierced by large diactines. A specialized ostia-bearing zone, located below the osculum, leads the incurrent water flow to inhalant cavities.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="253" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="50.[114,647,1462,1704]" box="[114,258,1462,1488]" pageId="50" pageNumber="253">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[114,647,1462,1704]" pageId="50" pageNumber="253">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirk" authorityYear="1895" box="[114,220,1493,1518]" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" genus="Lamontia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="50" pageNumber="253" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[114,220,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="253">Lamontia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a particular sponge, which bears a number of similarities with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miklucho-Maclay" authorityYear="1870" box="[416,484,1524,1549]" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" genus="Baeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="50" pageNumber="253" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[416,484,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="253">Baeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The choanoskeleton is composed of microdiactines, and there are pugioles in the skeleton of the exhalant aquiferous system. It is distinguished by a special ostiabearing zone and large diactines, which make the sponge hispid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
